  "text": "Servo uses an external style system (Stylo) rather than maintaining local style and selectors crates. The Servo repository (servo/servo) depends on crates from https://github.com/servo/stylo via git dependencies specified in the main Cargo.toml (lines 160, 178): 'selectors' and 'stylo' (which provides the style functionality). These external crates define the style parsing and selector matching capabilities that Servo uses throughout its components (layout, script, fonts, etc.). The test file at tests/unit/style/lib.rs serves as the main integration point for testing the style system in Servo.\n\nThe Rust compiler does NOT share or depend on Servo's selectors crate. However, Rust provides a critical proc_macro bridge mechanism in library/proc_macro/src/bridge/ that enables procedural macros (including those potentially used in Servo's build scripts) to communicate with the compiler. The bridge is defined in library/proc_macro/src/bridge/mod.rs and consists of client-server RPC infrastructure with serialization support (Encode/Decode traits in rpc.rs). The key communication configuration is handled by BridgeConfig, which establishes a closure-based dispatch mechanism between clients and servers. The bridge modules (client.rs, server.rs, rpc.rs) implement handle management and type-safe message passing using handle counters and state stores."
}

